--------when updating pythonanywhere host----------------
apply the following commands in bash to avoid deleting files when merged
(for files not present in the git rep)

$ git stash
$ git fetch
$ git merge FETCH_HEAD
$ git stash apply --index

---------for uploading to github------------
$ git status
(shows changed and so on)

$ git commit -a -m "commit msg"
adds changes made and commints the with msg

$ git remote add origin "https://github.com/<your-github-username>/my-first-blog.git"
(whats provided by github

$ git push -u origin master
(push changes to github)

--aditional information for setting up git--

git config --list (gets the info of config file)

$ git init
$ git config --global user.name "Your Name"
$ git config --global user.email you@example.com
(for first initializing git MUST BE RUN IN ROOT DIR)




